{"action": "edit", "code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = extend_red_pixels(input_grid)\n    return output_grid\ndef extend_red_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes in a numpy array of a grid with different colored pixels and extends each red pixel upwards\n    until it reaches the edge or a non-gray pixel. If the next pixel to the right is gray, it extends the red pixel\n    one grid to the right and continues to extend upwards. The function returns the modified grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    - input_grid: a numpy array of shape (n, m) representing the input grid\n    \n    Returns:\n    - output_grid: a numpy array of shape (n, m) representing the modified grid\n    \"\"\"\n    output_grid = np.copy(input_grid)\n    n, m = input_grid.shape\n    for i in range(n):\n        for j in range(m):\n            if output_grid[i][j] == red:\n                k = i - 1\n                while k >= 0 and output_grid[k][j] == grey:\n                    output_grid[k][j] = red\n                    if j < m - 1 and output_grid[k][j + 1] == grey:\n                        j += 1\n                    k -= 1\n    return output_grid", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = `traverse each red pixels extend it upward, extend one grid to the right if the next grid is gray and continue to extend upwards until the edge`(input_grid)\n    return output_grid", "gpt_code": "def extend_red_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes in a numpy array of a grid with different colored pixels and extends each red pixel upwards\n    until it reaches the edge or a non-gray pixel. If the next pixel to the right is gray, it extends the red pixel\n    one grid to the right and continues to extend upwards. The function returns the modified grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    - input_grid: a numpy array of shape (n, m) representing the input grid\n    \n    Returns:\n    - output_grid: a numpy array of shape (n, m) representing the modified grid\n    \"\"\"\n    output_grid = np.copy(input_grid)\n    n, m = input_grid.shape\n    for i in range(n):\n        for j in range(m):\n            if output_grid[i][j] == red:\n                k = i - 1\n                while k >= 0 and output_grid[k][j] == grey:\n                    output_grid[k][j] = red\n                    if j < m - 1 and output_grid[k][j + 1] == grey:\n                        j += 1\n                    k -= 1\n    return output_grid", "holes": {"extend_red_pixels": "traverse each red pixels extend it upward, extend one grid to the right if the next grid is gray and continue to extend upwards until the edge"}}
